      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAZZY MCGRAW (7) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 1.75 lengths second (26.17) in a Grade 5 at this track. Will find this more suitable and can atone. GO WILD BLUE (5) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 7 lengths at this track in a handy 25.49 beating ROSMARINO. Awkwardly drawn but goes well at this distance. Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Expecting another bold showing. RACCOON RHIA (1) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 9 lengths back in third (26.16) at this track in a Grade 5 over 450m. Likely to be in the finish again. MAGICAL DEE (2) finished in the placings last start and deserves some thought.",
